Asus has revealed its latest ROG Swift desktop monitor at Computex 2017. The ROG Swift PG35VQ boasts a 35-inch curved display with a resolution of 3,440 x 1,440 and an ultrawide 21:9 aspect ratio. A maximum refresh rate of 200Hz coupled with support for Nvidia’s G-Sync technology offers smooth gameplay without screen tearing, said the company. The monitor also conforms to the HDR10 display standard and has a maximum brightness of 1,000cd/m². A combination of 512 individual LED backlights and localised dimming also allows for an increased contrast range. Other features include Asus Aura RGB lighting and a robust stand with multiple adjustment options. Pricing and release date information for the monitor is currently not available.